The paper discusses the problem of recognising visual objects in different forms, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also evaluates classification, domain adaptation, and deep learning methods, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of spatial relations between parts in modelling object classes, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
